      • newID

        public static String newID(int userNumber)
        Returns an 18 character ID comprised of user number and timestamp elements CMA120518 A new wrinkle has occurred. This ID is broken into subdirectories like aaaaaaaa/bbbb/ccc/ddd Microsoft Windows dos not allow certain patterns for file or direcotry names : http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/aa365247%28v=vs.85%29.aspx

        Do not use the following reserved device names for the name of a file:
        CON, PRN, AUX, NUL, COM1, COM2, COM3, COM4, COM5, COM6, COM7, COM8, COM9, LPT1, LPT2, LPT3, LPT4, LPT5, LPT6, LPT7, LPT8, and LPT9. Also avoid these names followed immediately by an extension; for example, NUL.txt is not recommended. For more information, see Namespaces.

        Parameters:
        userNumber - the user number to be incorporated into the new ID
        Returns:
        an 18 character ID comprised of user number and timestamp elements

      • encodeURIComponent

        public static String encodeURIComponent(String s)
        Creates a percent encoded string. The original string is extracted using the UTF-8 codeset. We may NOT use URLEncoder.encode(param[0], "UTF-8") because it converts (' ' to '+')
        See Also:
        https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986
